Trench Made & We Only Going Up😈

🎵: Downfall 616

Thank you to premier Tim Houston of Nova Scotia for taking time out of his day to sit down with me & talk about plans to give back to the city.

Also, it was great to finally get the chance to sit down with students from schools across Halifax/Dartmouth & share my story! Grateful to be in the position to inspire you all 💙
They Been Tryna Catch Up Wit Me I’m Just Already Far 🤷🏽‍♂️

Man words can’t describe how grateful and blessed I am to be in a position to give back to my community! This is way bigger then me. I’m proud to say the “Lindell Wigginton Skills Academy” last weekend was a huge success! I appreciate the support from my community, family, and friends who helped in any way to make the Skills Academy a reality for all the participants! I would like to thank the organizers, sponsors, staff, volunteers, and parents for their time & support for making this camp as successful as it was! I’m already looking forward to next year! 

Thank you!!! 💙🤍💛

Lindell Wigginton is the REAL DEAL! The 6’1” PG was one of the coldest guards in the G League last season and then made HISTORY with the @bucks. He averaged a career-high 22.3 PPG and 6.0 APG for the @wisconsinherd - with a 41 point game a multiple nights of 30+. 🦌 @rnstmojo 

Lindell then proved his worth at the NBA level when he posted 25 PTS & 11 AST for the Bucks in his first career start - this made him the first player since Isiah Thomas to drop 25-10 in his first NBA start. Wigginton is a HOOPER. He has a wicked handle, has become a much improved shooter over the years, and will surprise you with his ability to lock down on defense. Hope we can see him on a full-time NBA deal soon!
